The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 June is 278,081 (32,050.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 June, there were 698 new confirmed cases (80.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 May, there were 651 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 7% (47 extra cases).
